AUDIO: 'are quite blurry, but after plugging it through this AI, look how much details it adds to the hair and the face. This is really good for sharpening or upscaling images. Let me zoom in a bit more so you can see the clear difference'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in definition and detail. And then finally, here\'s a night sky comparison. So, here\'s the before, and here\'s the after. Again, just much sharper in detail. And then here are'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'some of their official examples for your reference as well. In fact, how this works is very interesting. It\'s called pixel diffusion because it works in what is called pixel space. You see how normal image generators work is they use'

[02:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a decoder that turns the image data from a compressed latent space back into pixels that you and I can see. But how this PID works is that it does the decoding in pixel space instead. So, if'

[02:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you\'re generating an image with one of the top models out there like Flux or Z Image or even Stable Diffusion, that model will first generate the image in pixel space and then PID can take this'

[02:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'latent as a guidance, but it directly denoises that image in high resolution pixel space. And this can produce sharper 4K results with fewer artifacts that you often find with traditional'

[02:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'upscaler methods. Now, if you compare PID to other upscaling methods, especially to one of the leading ones called SeedVR2, you can see that PID is just a lot more consistent and detailed.'

[02:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, notice that as I zoom in to various parts of the image, the quality and consistency and coherence of PID is just a lot better than SeedVR2. Here\'s another example for your reference.'

[03:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Notice that PID is just a lot sharper and more detailed compared to SeedVR2. And it\'s also more faithful. Like the texture of the plushies look a lot more realistic than what we got from SeedVR2,'

[03:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which looks like it\'s kind of just making stuff up. Then here\'s another example. If we look at SeedVR2, notice that if you zoom way in, the edges are super blurry, they\'re not really defined well, and there\'s kind of some'

[03:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'artifacts. But if you look at PID, it just looks really sharp and good. Now, not only is the quality great, but it\'s also really lightweight and incredibly fast. So, here\'s the latency and as you can see, PID can upscale an image in'

[03:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'less than a second, up to 5.9 times faster than Seed VR 2, which has indeed been very slow for me. And then on the right is the win rate of PID versus the other image upscaling methods. And as'

[04:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
